Have you ever wanted to play video games while also contributing to science? In psychology experiments developed by myself and Peter Battaglia, participants are immersed in an interactive 3D world which is experimentally well-controlled, yet also extremely fun. This talk will explain how we created these "game-like" experiments in Python using the Panda3D video game engine.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Jessica Hamrick,Peter Battaglia</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 13 Apr 2014 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.pyvideo.org/video/2655/games-for-science-creating-interactive-psycholog</guid><enclosure url="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b8VsDmx7qdE" length="None" type="video/flv"></enclosure><media:thumbnail url="http://i1.ytimg.com/vi/b8VsDmx7qdE/hqdefault.jpg"></media:thumbnail></item></channel></rss>